i## Updating PowerDNS		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe latest PowerDNS 4.2 version isn't included in the Debian 10		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isoftware repository. You'll need to download it from the Debian		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iUnstable repository. However, since PowerDNS depends on numerous new		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ilibrary files — including essential system libraries — installing		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ivia commands like `apt-get install -t unstable pdns-server` would		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iupgrade some core system files to Unstable versions.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIn this situation, Docker is the best solution. Since we only need to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
idownload PowerDNS from the Debian repository without compiling it		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iourselves, we can create the image with just a few lines:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
