i## Configuring the GeoIP Database		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iPowerDNS uses the MaxMind GeoIP database for IP geographical		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iinformation. Although MaxMind provides a free, lower-precision IP		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
igeolocation database (GeoLite) for personal use, starting December 30,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i2019, MaxMind began requiring GeoLite users to register an account and		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iobtain a license key to download the database. The steps are as		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifollows:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i1. Go to the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
h   GeoLite 2 Databases page	URL:https://dev.maxmind.com/geoip/geoip2/geolite2/	{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   , click the yellow button at the bottom to register. This process		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   requires email verification and cannot be done through a proxy (since		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   that's what they specialize in).		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i2. In the account details page, click `My License Key` on the left to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   manage license keys.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i3. Click `Generate License Key` to create a new key.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i4. Fill in a key description and select the key version as shown in		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   the image, then confirm with the blue button:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
I   - License version selection	/usr/uploads/202001/maxmind-license-version.png	{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i5. After submission, note two important pieces of information to fill		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   in the configuration file later:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - `Account/User ID`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - `License Key`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iNext, you can use MaxMind's official `geoipupdate` tool to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iautomatically update the database. First, install it on Debian:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
