i## Configuring and Starting PowerDNS		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iTo enable GeoIP functionality, modify PowerDNS's configuration file.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iOpen `pdns.conf` and make the following changes based on your existing		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iworking PowerDNS configuration:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Enable Lua records		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  enable-lua-records=yes		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Add geoip after your current database backend		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  launch=gmysql,geoip		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Specify the database file path, using the highest-precision city-level database		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  geoip-database-files=/etc/geoip/GeoLite2-City.mmdb		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThen start PowerDNS. If your host system is Debian Unstable, simply		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
irun:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  systemctl start pdns		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
