i## Adding Lua Resolution Records		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIn modern DNS resolution systems, DNS servers typically inform		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iupstream servers of the user's IP step by step (known as EDNS),		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iallowing servers to assign the nearest server address based on the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iuser's IP.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIn PowerDNS Lua, the user's IP address is available as the variable `bestwho` .		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iHowever, if the user's DNS server doesn't inform upstream servers of		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe user's address, `bestwho` will point to the DNS server's address.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFirst, let's demonstrate how to use `bestwho` . Create a record of		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
itype `LUA` with the following content:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  A ";if(bestwho:isIPv4()) then return bestwho:toString() else return '0.0.0.0' end"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe initial `A` indicates the record type to return. The following		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
istring is a small Lua program: if the source IP is IPv4, it returns		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe user's IP; otherwise, it returns `0.0.0.0` to indicate failure.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSimilarly, we can create an IPv6 version. Create another record with		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe same name and type `LUA` :		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  AAAA ";if(bestwho:isIPv6()) then return bestwho:toString() else return '::' end"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iOr use a TXT record to return connection information with port		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
inumbers:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  TXT "bestwho:toStringWithPort()"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iOr use a LOC record to return the geographical location inferred by		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iGeoIP:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  LOC "latlonloc()"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iAll these features can be seen at `whoami.lantian.pub` :		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
