i## Configuring GeoDNS		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iNow that we understand how PowerDNS Lua works, we can configure		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iregional resolution records. PowerDNS provides a convenient function `pickclosest`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithat automatically selects the nearest server from an IP list for the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iuser. For example, the current A record for `lantian.pub` is:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  A "pickclosest({'103.42.215.193','185.186.147.110','107.172.134.89','195.154.221.59'})"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i`pickclosest` also works for AAAA records:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  AAAA "pickclosest({'2001:470:19:10bb::1','2001:470:d:46e::1','2001:470:1f07:54d::1','2001:470:1f13:28::1'})"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i(The above servers are located in: Hong Kong, Los Angeles, New York,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand France respectively)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThis way, users from different regions get different resolution		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iresults:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
