i## Country-Based Resolution		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iInstead of selecting the nearest server based on geographical		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ilocation, a better approach is country-based resolution — for		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iexample, the common setup of direct connections within China and using		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iCloudflare abroad. PowerDNS provides a useful function for this: `country` :		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  TXT ";if(country('CN')) then return 'YES' else return 'NO' end"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iTest from inside and outside China:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Mainland China		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  $ dig +short @103.42.215.193 TXT is-china.lantian.pub		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  "YES"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Los Angeles, USA		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  $ dig +short @103.42.215.193 TXT is-china.lantian.pub		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  "NO"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSlightly modifying this code allows distributing traffic between China		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iand overseas to different servers for A, AAAA, CNAME, etc.:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  CNAME ";if(country('CN')) then return 'cdn-china.lantian.pub' else return 'cdn-overseas.lantian.pub' end"		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
